[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81574] [1862919] [debug] Token: List::MoreUtils. Extra: 0 >- Provide the stuff missing in List::Util<
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81576] [1862919] [debug] Token: List::MoreUtils. Extra: 1 >- https://metacpan.org/pod/List::MoreUtils<
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81787] [1862919] [debug] Line 63: >o List::Util<
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81792] [1862919] [debug] Token: List::Util. Extras:
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81794] [1862919] [debug] 	- use List::Util 'any' or, better, 'first' (but don't use first() for finding 0 or undef!)
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81796] [1862919] [debug] 	- And then 1 of
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81797] [1862919] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ eq $thing } @values) ...
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81799] [1862919] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ == $thing } @values) ...
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81800] [1862919] [debug] 	- It's not limited to just string or number comparison of course; you can
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81802] [1862919] [debug] 	put any arbitrary code in there. if(any { $_->is_close_to(123.45) } @values) ...
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81803] [1862919] [debug] 	- Or
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81804] [1862919] [debug] 	- If you don't like the XSUB call overhead of List::Util::any, there's
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81806] [1862919] [debug] 	another (non-core) CPAN module List::Keywords which implements many of
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81807] [1862919] [debug] 	the same utilities as real keywords with real opcodes, so they run
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81809] [1862919] [debug] 	faster.
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81810] [1862919] [debug] 	- use List::Keywords 'any';
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81811] [1862919] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ eq $thing } @values) ...
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81813] [1862919] [debug] 	- Or
[2026-04-10 19:48:19.81814] [1862919] [debug] 	- if (grep { $_ eq $myval } @arr)
